getMxNames

public Set<String> getMxNames(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
                       throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Returns a set of found person names. First for all administration persons are searched. Then, all persons are removed from the matching set, for whom a related business person object exists. This new set is returned.

Overrides:
getMxNames in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO

matrix.util.MatrixException - if the query for person objects failed

parse

protected void parse(String _url,
                     String _content)

Parses all person specific URL values. This includes:

  • assigned groups
  • assigned roles
  • access
  • business administration access
  • is person inactive
  • flag if the person is an application user
  • flag if the person is a full user
  • flag if the person is a business administrator
  • flag if the person is a system administrator
  • flag if the person is a trusted person
  • person wants email
  • person wants icon mail
  • address
  • email address
  • fax number
  • full name
  • default vault
  • phone number
  • password never expires flag

If an _url is included in IGNORED_URLS, this URL is ignored.

Overrides:
parse in class AbstractUser_mxJPO
Parameters:
_url - URL to parse
_content - content depending on the URL
See Also:

protected String getExportMQL()

writeObject

protected void writeObject(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           Appendable _out)
                    throws IOException
Writes specific information about the cached administration person to the given TCL update file _out. The included information is
  • password never expires flag (if parameter PARAM_IGNORE_PSWD_NEVER_EXPIRES is not set)
  • access
  • business administration access
  • person wants email (if parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_EMAIL is not set)
  • person wants icon mail (if parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_ICON_MAIL is not set)
  • address
  • email address
  • fax number
  • full name
  • phone number
  • default vault
  • default application (if defined)
  • assigned groups
  • assigned roles

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to
  • reset the comment (description)
  • set the version and author attribute
  • reset all not ignored attributes
  • define the TCL variable "OBJECTID" with the object id of the represented business object
  • sets the password never expires flag to false (means that the password expires); depends on parameter PARAM_IGNORE_PSWD_NEVER_EXPIRES
  • disables that the person wants email; depends on parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_EMAIL
  • enables that the person wants icon mail; depends on parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_ICON_MAIL
The original method of the super class if called surrounded with a history off, because if the update itself is done the modified basic attribute and the version attribute of the business object is updated.
The new generated MQL code is set in the front of the already defined MQL code in _preMQLCode and appended to the MQL statements in _postMQLCode.

Overrides:
update in class AbstractUser_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
See Also:
PARAM_IGNORE_PSWD_NEVER_EXPIRES, PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_EMAIL, PARAM_IGNORE_WANTS_ICON_MAIL

ignoreWorkspaceObjects

protected boolean ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)

Calculates if workspace objects for this person are not handled. This is done by checking if the name of this person matches one of the match lists defined with parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_PERSONS. In this case the the workspace objects are ignored for this person.

Overrides:
ignoreWorkspaceObjects in class AbstractUser_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Returns:
true if the handling of workspace objects for this person is ignored
See Also:
PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_PERSONS
